Colombia ' s peso ends slightly lower at 998 . 60 . Colombia ' s peso gave up gains that pushed it to an intraday high of 996 and closed 40 centavos lower at 998 . 60 in active trading on the country ' s interbank market , dealers said . They said dollar - selling by coffee and oil exporters buoyed the peso in early trade , lifting it well above the psychological barrier of 1 , 000 to the dollar . But the peso came under pressure later in the day from banks and other financial institutions that stepped in to buy cheap greenbacks . Dealers reported a higher - than - average 316 trades for a total of $ 118 million . - - Juan Guillermo Londono , Bogota newsroom , 571 610 7944 
